Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Remove the @pork chops{2} from the refrigerator and
allow to come to room temperature. Meanwhile, soak the @wooden skewers{4} in
water in a #shallow dish{}. Halve, peel, and slice the @red onion{1}(halved and
sliced into 1/2-inch wedges). Halve, core, seed, and remove the white ribs from
the @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, seeded, and ribbed). Then, cut into
1-inch cubes. Cut the @Yukon gold potatoes{12} and @zucchini{1} into 1/2-inch
cubes. Mince the @oregano{1}(minced) and @mint{1}(minced) leaves. Zest and halve
the @lemon{1}, then cut one half into 4 wedges. Mince or grate the @garlic{2}.

== Kebabs ==

Assemble the kebabs: thread the bell pepper, onion, zucchini, potatoes, and
lemon wedges onto skewers, mixing up the order as you go. In a #small bowl{},
combine half the lemon zest, half the garlic, @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}, and a
large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Drizzle over the skewers and
roast on a #baking sheet{} for ~{20-25%minutes}, until lightly caramelized.

> If you have a grill, cook the skewers there! Remember to rotate half way
> through cooking.

== Pork Chops ==

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Season the pork chops on both sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the pork
chops to the pan and cook ~{4-5%minutes} per side, until golden brown and
cooked to desired doneness (we like medium-well!).

> If you have a grill, fire it up to medium and cook the chops there!

== Oregano-Mint Pesto ==

While the pork cooks, make the oregano-mint pesto: in a small bowl{}, combine
the oregano, mint, remaining garlic, remaining lemon zest, @olive oil{2%tbsp},
and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Serve the pork chops alongside the veggie kebabs. Squeeze a roasted lemon
wedge over the veggies. Spoon the oregano-mint pesto over the pork and enjoy!